cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on dialog systems and proposes a new method to address the problem of multiple valid next utterances in goal-oriented dialog. This is a core area of research in computational linguistics. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new method that combines supervised learning and reinforcement learning approaches to improve the performance of goal-oriented dialog systems. This falls under the broader area of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.LG (Learning) - The paper proposes a new learning method for goal-oriented dialog systems that takes into account the problem of multiple valid next utterances. This falls under the area of machine learning. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper discusses existing end-to-end neural methods for dialog and proposes a new method that improves their performance. This falls under the area of neural computing. 
5. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a new testbed, permuted-bAbI dialog tasks, to evaluate goal-oriented dialog systems in a more realistic setting. This falls under the area of software engineering as it involves designing and implementing a software system for testing purposes.
